    {
        "content": "<p>The context is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Real.Gamma_ofNat_eq_factorial#doc\">docs#Real.Gamma_ofNat_eq_factorial</a>, which seems to follow the antipattern of using <code>ofNat</code> on one side of the equation, and skipping it on the other. Despite this, the lemma actually half-works as intended!</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">natLit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">36</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Gamma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">37</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Gamma_ofNat_eq_factorial</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- miraculously does the right thing</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">guard_target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=ₛ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">factorial</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">36</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Gamma_ofNat_eq_factorial</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- makes a mess</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- goal is `Real.Gamma (OfNat.ofNat (36 + 1)) = x`</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 494695952,
